    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-09T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="7"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00/838: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Earle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-09T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 9, 1934—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 9—8:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. The Austrian Government after weeks of experimenting with a policy of clemency
                    towards local Nazis decided last night to make full use of summary justice
                    decree (see telegram 65, November 11th, 1933). Dollfuss apparently has given in
                    to pressure within Government circles to fight Nazi terrorism with strong arm
                    methods after having been finally convinced that all other methods were
                    futile.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
